{"lemma":"كُلّابِ","slug":"كُلّابِ","root":"ك.ل.ب","root_slug":"ك-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37148","n37149","n37151","n37152"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pike pole, gaff"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hook; fishhook"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hook; tenterhook"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hook; grapple, grapnel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hook; fleshhook"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hook; billhook, pruning-hook","examples":[{"text":"ويحتاج [الزعرور] إلى التسبيخ كل سنة وقد يسبخ الشجر كله ويخفف ورقها عنها بكلاب حديد مصفى حاد ماض فإن الحديد إذا دخل شيء من صدأه بعض أغصانها لهلكها وأبطلها […]","english":"[The azarole] needs to be plucked every year (and the whole tree may be plucked), trimming its leaves with a sharp iron hook, such as when the iron enters some rust it razes and fordoes it. […]"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clamp"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spur"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"talons, especially of a falcon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thorns"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of كَلْب (kalb, “dog”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From كَلْب (kalb, “dog”) in the sense of “a predatory animal”, “a dog or a falcon”, connected especially to canine teeth or claws; “to pierce”, as well as the conception of “hunting or catching food”, “a tool or aid in acquiring food”. The sense of a clamp is borrowed from Aramaic ܟܰܠܒܬ݂ܳܐ (kalbṯā, “tongs, pincers; metal device used to hold something”) which also developed from the proto-Semitic sense of a claw, while the sense of a “hook” is attested in the construct state and hence reckoned an Aramaism after Classical 